\f0\fs20 \cf0 Irrational entrepreneurs would probably have an even greater incentive to force creditors to accept a loss. Creditors are generally "faceless"---markets, banks or large lending institutions---so exploiting one does not evoke the same moral code as when dealing with people who make personal loans (STUDY). Moreover, a failed business affects more than just the entrepreneurs pocketbook. It affects, among other things, his pride, sense of self-worth and standing within his community [][#Kahneman2011].}

